
Networks prerequisites at various schools:

BU: 

http://www.cs.bu.edu/CourseMap/Home.html

In particular, CS330 (Algorithms) is shown as a prerequisite
for CS 455/655: Computer Networks
 
Some offerings of Networks make Algorithms a co-requisite, but
Discrete Mathematics with probability (MA293) is a prerequisite:

http://www.cs.bu.edu/fac/byers/cs455.html
Prerequisites: CS 350 (Systems) and MA 293 (Discrete Mathematics with 
elementary probability theory) (or equivalent discrete math and basic 
probability background) are prerequisites for taking this course, while 
CS 330 (Algorithms) is a strongly recommended co-requisite.

